  <title>Open an entity or a set of entities</title>

  <p>To open one or more entity you have to use the <em>open entities</em>
  dialog, which is opened by default when starting the program.</p>

  <p>To open the dialog from the editor, click on the <gui>Open</gui> button
  <media type="image" mime="image/png" src="figures/open-button.png"/></p>

  <media type="image" mime="image/png" src="figures/open-dialog.png"/>

  <p>To search for an entity by its label, type it in the search entry,
  then click on the result to open it in the editor.</p>

  <section id="open-multiple-entities">
  <title>Open multiple entities</title>
  <p>To select more than one entity, click on the <gui>Select</gui> button
  <media type="image" mime="image/png" src="figures/select-button.png"/>
  then pin the checks of the entities you want to open.</p>

  <p>To select or deselect all the entities displayed,
  press on the central headerbar.</p>

  <note style="tip"><p>You can select the row of an entity clicking
  on the row or by pressing the <key>Space</key> button when the row
  is selected.</p></note>
